{
  "text": "The number of alleles (n), number of effective alleles (n e ), frequency of allele, expected (H e ) and observed (H o ) heterozygosity, polymorphic information content (PIC), and probability of identity (PI) were calculated using the software Microsoft Office Excel and the freeware program for analysis of microsatellite data IDENTITY 1.0 programme (http://www.uni-graz.at/~sefck/). The H o was calculated as the ratio between the number of heterozygous individuals and total number of genotypes per locus, H e according to the formula H e = 1-∑p i 2 [CITATION_1] . The PIC, effective number of alleles (n e ), and PI values were calculated as: 1-∑p i 2 -∑p i 4 (p i is the frequency of i th allele), n e = (∑p i 2 ) -1 [CITATION_2] , and 2*(∑p i 2 ) 2 -∑p i 4 [CITATION_3] , respectively. The software PAST [CITATION_4] was used for cluster analysis. The unweighted pair-group average method (UPGMA) was used for dendrogram construction based on Jaccard's similarity coefficients.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12939636",
    "[CITATION_2]": "84226196",
    "[CITATION_3]": "42406954",
